🪙 PantheonOS Module — Universal Identity & Credit Layer (UICL v1.0)

I. Canonical Statement

Known, the actor must be.
Attributed, the action must be.
Valued, the contribution becomes.
Flow, the credit does.

⸻

II. Definition

The Universal Identity & Credit Layer (UICL) is the trust and value backbone that:

* anchors who participates (identity)
* tracks what they contribute (attribution)
* assigns how much it matters (credit)
* enables value flow across systems (exchange)

It binds:

* BLP (who is connected)
* CE (what is transformed)
* CMP (how value flows)

⸻

