VI. Credit Mechanics

1. Attribution Split

Every output distributes credit:

Input Provider → %
Converter → %
System / Platform → %
Downstream Contributors → %

⸻

2. Credit Properties

* Composable → can combine across systems
* Traceable → origin always known
* Transferable → usable across domains
* Decay-aware → outdated value fades
* Confidence-weighted → uncertainty priced in

⸻

3. Credit ≠ Money (Important)

Money = static exchange
Credit = meaning-weighted contribution value

Money can be derived from credit
Not the other way around

